The governorship candidate of the Social Democratic Party (SDP) in Rivers State, Senator Magnus Abe, has said if elected, his administration will integrate new ways of doing things in the state. Abe disclosed this on Wednesday while receiving hundreds of decampees from other political parties to the SDP in Okrika LGA of the state. SDP senatorial candidate pledges free education in Kwara South Why Nigerians should dump APC, PDP – SDP presidential candidate He said his administration will never impose leaders on the people but allow communities to choose their leaders, who will in turn guide the government on what to do for the people. “We have talked to you about freedom, liberty and respect for norms and institutions. We will ensure that we give you back the right to choose your leaders. It is the people you choose as leaders that we will deal with,” he said. 